Police were already on the scene when paramedics arrived. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained several gunshot wounds to his chest and arms and was in a critical condition said ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring. Paramedics immediately began their treatment and provided the patient with several advanced life support interventions. Once treated the patient was transported to a nearby hospital. Unfortunately on route to hospital the patient s vital signs diminished. Paramedics initiated CPR for some time. After a short time no vital signs returned and the man was declared dead Meiring said.He was unable to provide any further details.